(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
(In real study situations, students master Probability by practising with tasks that) Tj
T*
(mirror simple events, combined events, and complements. The topic becomes more) Tj
T*
(meaningful when it is linked to examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that) Tj
T*
(reflect how Mathematics is assessed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on finding the probability of drawing a particular card) Tj
T*
(or rolling a number.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in sample spaces, favorable outcomes, and probability rules) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Probability step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on simple events, combined events, and) Tj
T*
(complements.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid counting outcomes incorrectly or forgetting total outcomes) Tj
T*
(while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
